The paper is about motion planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The use of sequential simplifications and quotient-spaces is a common technique in motion planning algorithms, which suggests that the paper could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The algorithm presented in the paper involves random sampling and tree growth, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV), respectively.
